description:
Natixis Corporate & Investment Banking is a leading global financial institution that provides advisory, investment banking, financing, corporate banking and capital markets services to corporations, financial institutions, financial sponsors and sovereign and supranational organizations worldwide.




Our teams of experts in close to 30 countries advise clients on their strategic development, helping them to grow and transform their businesses, and maximize their positive impact. Natixis CIB is committed to aligning its financing portfolio with a carbon neutrality path by 2050 while helping its clients reduce the environmental impact of their business.




As part of the Global Financial Services division of Groupe BPCE, the second largest banking group in France through the Banque Populaire and Caisse d’Epargne retail networks, Natixis CIB benefits from the Group’s financial strength and solid financial ratings (Standard & Poor's: A, Moody's: A1, Fitch Ratings: A+, R&I: A+).




Main Responsibilities:




You will be a part of Natixis Front Office team, in charge of a portfolio of Infrastructure, Energy, and

Aviation Finance transactions;

 * Perform credit analysis, rating/LGD proposals for these clients. Preparation and presentation to
 * Credit Committee of annual reviews;
 * Monitoring of the transactions (waivers, updates…) and regular updates to management on these topics
 * Regular interaction with internal parties (Coverage, Origination, Risk Dept and other relevant Dept) and external parties (client, external counsels) for the preparation of these analysis and the monitoring of the deals
 * Monitor the profitability of the transactions you are in charge of. Propose portfolio strategies on these deals (secondary sales, credit insurance…) and direct Distribution teams for execution of the trades
 * Open on all new transactions presented to Credit Committee with a portfolio angle (benchmarking with other similar transactions in the books; analysis of its profitability and liquidity in the secondary market)




Required Skills




 * University Degree holder in Finance, Accounting, or related discipline;
 * Minimum 1-2 years of experience in Structured Finance and/or Credit Risk with exposure to the Infrastructure and/or Commodity and/or Aviation sectors;
 * Comfortable communicating with senior management members;
 * Excellent English language skills;
 * Team player and strong interpersonal skills;
 * Ability to work under tight deadline.

Main Responsibilities




Involvement in monthly/ quarterly reporting cycles of Net Operating Income, Adjusted Net Income actuals / forecast, Total Global Expense Report, EBITDA actuals and forecast, Budgeting forecast, re-forecast, gathering data for attribution analysis, S&P liquidity report, external financing covenants calculation etc.




Provide accurate, timely, and actionable financial information and key business metrics to stakeholders;




Maintain existing models and metrics, while help improving or developing new analytical frameworks that enhance insight, efficiency and decision-making speed;




Collaborate with functional departments across the company as part of the reporting process;




Highlights risks, spots opportunities, builds simulations and sensitivity analyses, and suggests solutions that create value for stakeholders;




Ad hoc project work.




Mandatory




Required skills and capabilities:




Strong understanding of P&L, balance sheet and cash flow dynamics, and fluency in general accounting principles and rules;




Passionate about the data business;




Advanced knowledge of MS Excel;




Fluent in English;




Optional




Understanding of main real estate and investment management metrics;




Experience in financial reporting in accordance with a major accounting framework (IFRS, US GAAP);




Understanding of fund, property and SPV accounting;




General




Ability to thrive in a growth environment, adapt to changing circumstances and work autonomously;




Able to prioritise on a daily basis and managing several competing deadlines;




A self-starter who is able to prioritize and manage multiple assignments, take initiative, and work independently;




An analytical, creative thinker who can focus on the details without losing sight of the big picture.

Role:




- Drive awareness and engagement among stakeholders, working closely with various teams, exhibiting project management




- Develop and implement communication strategies to effectively communicate the benefits and impacts of people & culture initiatives to internal and external stakeholders;




- Create and manage a comprehensive communication plan, including the delivery of key messages, timeline, and stakeholder engagement activities;




- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure consistent messaging and alignment with organizational goals;




- Lead the creation of compelling and effective communication content, including reports, presentations, newsletters, emails, and intranet articles and success case videos;




- Manage internal communication channels, including the intranet, and digital signage (everything related to internal employer branding);




- Conduct stakeholder analysis and develop tailored communication strategies to effectively reach different audience groups;




- Monitor and measure the effectiveness of communication and change efforts and make recommendations for improvement;




Skills Persona :




- 7+ years of experience (4+ years in a combination of experience in communications, event management)




- Degree in Mass Media, Marketing, Journalism/Communications, or a related field;




- Proven experience leading communication for people & culture initiatives/ projects (offline and online) in dynamic organization




- Excellent written and verbal communication skills, for different/ varied audiences;




- Strong stakeholder management and relationship-building skills;




- Strong project management skills, with the ability to manage communications throughout multiple - projects and priorities simultaneously;




- Ability to create compelling communication material with the use of the latest technologies for digital content creation incl. videos, newsletters and social media feeds; Strong problem-solving and analytical skills;




- Proficient in Google Suite, Notion




- Exposure/ understanding of content creation tools like Canva, Adobe will be preferred

Qualification : Diploma /BE (Mechanical/ Automobile)


 * Designing and producing visual interpretations of automobiles and their components using computer-aided design packages
 * Resolve engineering problems and find appropriate solutions;
 * Building prototypes of components, developing test procedures and conducting tests using software
 * Packages and physical testing methods;
 * Researching, designing and developing machinery and systems for automobiles;
 * Preparing material, cost and timing estimates, reports and design specifications;
 * Studying the energy, environmental and safety aspects of the planned work;
 * Investigating mechanical failures or unexpected maintenance problems;
 * Reviewing and approving designs, calculations and cost estimates;
 * To design, develop, build, test and modify models.
 * To design and analyze design control systems or algorithms.
 * To develop methodologies in calibration, engineering specifications and cost estimates for new design concepts, and control feature specifications and requirements.
 * Should have a min. 2-3 CAD/CAE software handling experience, CATIA V5, SOLID EDGE, SOLIDWORKS, CREO, CATIA, Autodesk inventor etc.
 * Hands on experience in Sheet Metal part design, mold design and die design
 * Create all levels of 3D & 2 D drawings for the bus with proper information for ease of Manufacturing and Assembly
 * To make assembly design incorporating manufacturing process.
 * Create drawings with GD& T & Tolerance Stack up in accordance to the process
 * Well versed with bus body standards and Design releases considering applicable legal requirements.
 * Knowledge of DFMEA, DFM, DFS, DFA and manufacturing technologies.
 * Preparation of Bill of material (BOM) & drawing release through PLM
